Insurance Summer '21 Release Notes

These release notes provide details about the changes in the Summer '21 release of Insurance.

Agent Permission Sets
Give your agents access to just what they need to complete their jobs with Agent Permission Sets.
Commissions at Producer and Product Level
As an insurance carrier, your organization uses commissions to incentivize your agents to grow your business. Now you have the flexibility to set up a variety of commission calculations that apply to individual agents and products in different time periods.

History Timelines with Insurance History LWC
You can configure the Insurance History Lightning web component to get a cohesive view of all things happening with a quote, claim, or policy.

Direct to Customer Quoting
Set up your customers and guest users to create and manage their own quotes with Direct to Customer Quoting.
Harmonized Insurance Claims Object Model
The Salesforce Claims product now supports both the existing Vlocity object model and the new Salesforce object model.

Server-Side Document Generation
Use server-side document generation for automatic or asynchronous invocation, and for documents with lots of token processing, tabulation, or line items.
Services for Insurance Summer '21
We've added new services and updated existing services for this release.

Data Model Updates for Insurance Summer '21
The data model updates for this release:
InsEnrollmentService: enrollMembers Coverage Check
The InsEnrollmentService: enrollMembers service checks whether plans selected by census members have coverages.

Insurance Summer '21 Minor Releases, Fixes, and Known Issues
This PDF provides details about the contents of this release. It also has package links for the minor releases that we add periodically.
